comment: A helper lemma for the value of a recursive definition generator on upper integers (typically either ` NN ` or ` NN0 ` ) with characteristic function ` F ( x , y ) ` and initial value ` A ` . Normally ` F ` is a function on the partition, and ` A ` is a member of the partition. See also comment in ~ om2uz0i . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 26-Jun-2013.) (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 18-Nov-2014.)
